feature-gated builds, may include) third-party dependencies that carry
obligations beyond a permissive licence. The audit deliverables under
audit/ enumerate these in full; the most material entries are reproduced
here for the benefit of redistributors:

  * evalexpr v12.x (https://github.com/ISibboI/evalexpr) is licensed
    AGPL-3.0-only and is consumed by `crates/model-compute` behind the
    feature flag `native`. When that feature is enabled (it is enabled in
    the default `larql-cli` build), the resulting binary is subject to
    AGPL-3.0 obligations, including the §13 network-distribution clause
    (offer source to remote users of a modified version exposed over a
    network). Corresponding source for evalexpr is available upstream;
    this project does not modify evalexpr.

  * webpki-roots / webpki-root-certs v1.0.x are licensed
    CDLA-Permissive-2.0 and are consumed transitively via
    ureq -> hf-hub -> larql-vindex. The CDLA Permissive 2.0 imposes no
    copyleft obligation; verbatim redistribution is permitted under the
    same terms.

See audit/dependency-licenses.md for the complete inventory and
